dataIdInfo.idAbs: Admin Lines. Layer was created by converting the Admin 3 polygon layer to lines.

Consts.useLimit: See the COD/FOD Registry Terms of Use. This does not replace any terms of use information provided with the dataset.

dataIdInfo.idPurp: Administrative boundary lines for level 0-3. Each line is attributed with the highest Admin level that it can represent.

dataLineage.statement:
Layer was created by ITOS by converting the Admin3 layer to lines. The lines were created after all processing on the Admin 3 layer had been completed by ITOS.
An 'AdminLevel' field is used to attribute the lines. The values used for this field are: (0,1,2,3,4,5,99). 99 represents coastline. 0 is international border, 1 is Admin1 border, 2 is Admin2 border, etc. Each line is attributed with the highest admin level that it can participate in. For example, if a boundary line is shared between an Admin 2 unit and an Admin 3 unit, it is attributed with an 'AdminLevel' value of "2".
